1d:T7341,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is PORTADOR SOS?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR SOS is a premium time-critical air logistics service for urgent cargo delivery, emergency shipment service, same-day air cargo, and next flight out logistics. It uses airport-linked movement, human support, air cargo timing checks, and a human operations desk."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How can I send urgent cargo today?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"You can send urgent cargo today by sharing the route, cargo type, weight, dimensions, deadline, and compliance details with PORTADOR SOS. The operations desk verifies pickup readiness, air cargo timing, airport cargo cargo handling, and fastest feasible support."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What does PORTADOR SOS include?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR SOS is a time-critical logistics solution for cargo that cannot wait for routine courier cycles. PORTADOR SOS plans the movement around airport access, direct air cargo coordination where feasible, documentation readiness, and a human operations desk watching the deadline."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When should I use PORTADOR SOS?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Use PORTADOR SOS when delay can cause business downtime, production loss, missed flights, tender rejection, event disruption, emergency replacement failure, or customer escalation. It is designed for urgency, not routine parcel movement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does same-day air cargo work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Same-day air cargo works by connecting urgent cargo to the fastest feasible air movement instead of waiting for routine courier routing. PORTADOR SOS coordinates pickup, airport support, airline cargo acceptance, flight movement, and destination support."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does next flight out cargo work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Next flight out cargo works by checking the earliest suitable airline connection for the shipment route, cargo type, and timing. PORTADOR SOS verifies feasibility, coordinates support, monitors flight-linked movement, and escalates exceptions through a human operations desk."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does airport-to-airport cargo work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Airport-to-airport cargo moves eligible shipments from one airport cargo terminal to another for faster intercity movement. It is useful when airport-linked movement is more important than routine door-to-door courier flow."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does airline cargo coordination work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Air cargo support means checking timing, cargo eligibility, documentation, handling requirements, and service feasibility before movement. PORTADOR SOS supports available air cargo options where the shipment is eligible."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR SOS arrange pickup?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR SOS can arrange urgent pickup in supported city zones and connect the shipment to the most suitable airport movement plan. Pickup feasibility depends on cargo readiness, traffic, air cargo timing, and route timing."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is this faster than regular courier?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For urgent intercity shipments, airport-linked execution can be faster because it is planned around the earliest feasible airline movement and avoids avoidable hub sorting delays. Routine courier is better for non-urgent parcel volume."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you handle B2B documents and parts?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR SOS supports urgent B2B documents and parts when timing, custody, and delivery matter. Common shipments include tender files, legal documents, spare parts, machine components, electronics, event material, pharma-support cargo, and high-value business shipments."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How can I send urgent machine parts?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Urgent machine parts can move through same-day air cargo, next flight out logistics, airport-to-airport cargo, or hand carry when feasible. PORTADOR SOS checks dimensions, weight, pickup readiness, air cargo timing, and destination support before support."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How can I move cargo after normal courier timing?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Cargo that misses a normal courier timing may still move through airport-linked urgent air cargo if airline timing, cargo handling, and pickup readiness allow it. PORTADOR SOS verifies feasibility instead of making a fake guarantee."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you support airport-to-airport delivery?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR SOS can coordinate airport-to-airport cargo where the route, documents, commodity, terminal process, and consignee delivery are feasible. This is useful when final-mile delivery is less important than fast intercity movement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What information is needed to quote?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A quote needs enough operational detail to check service feasibility, air cargo timing, and cargo acceptance. Share origin, destination, deadline, cargo type, weight, dimensions, pickup address, consignee details, invoice value, delivery requirement, and any battery, liquid, chemical, medical, or dangerous goods declaration."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR SOS operate outside business hours?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR SOS is built around 24x7 urgent logistics coordination, subject to airline schedules, airport terminal access, road pickup availability, documentation readiness, and regulatory acceptance."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR SOS support dangerous goods, lithium batteries, or regulated cargo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR SOS can check dangerous goods, lithium batteries, and regulated cargo, but final movement depends on airline rules, approval, and service feasibility. MSDS or declaration may be required, and packing, documentation, and regulatory compliance must be verified before support."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What cargo categories can PORTADOR SOS support?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR SOS can support urgent cargo categories that are eligible for air movement and properly documented. Common categories include B2B documents, machine parts, laptops, medical equipment, excess baggage, high-value cargo, lithium battery shipments, dangerous goods, event cargo, and aviation spares."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What cargo can move by air?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Air cargo can include urgent documents, machine parts, laptops, electronics cargo, medical equipment, event material, excess baggage, aviation spares, and high-value cargo when properly packed and documented. Restricted goods, DG cargo by air, lithium battery cargo, and chemical cargo approval depend on airline and regulatory acceptance."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What documents are needed for dangerous goods cargo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Dangerous goods cargo may require invoice, MSDS, shipper declaration, product classification, packing details, and compliance documents. PORTADOR SOS reviews documentation and regulatory compliance before support."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What affects urgent air cargo feasibility?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Urgent air cargo feasibility depends on timing, cargo type, documentation, serviceability, and regulatory requirements. Key factors include pickup readiness, air cargo timing, handling requirements, cargo dimensions, weight, commodity type, documentation, route availability, and receiver readiness."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When is next flight out required?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Next flight out is required when the shipment cannot wait for overnight courier or surface transport. It is used for AOG shipment India, urgent spare parts delivery, medical equipment cargo, tender document delivery, and emergency replacement shipment scenarios."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When is airport-to-airport cargo better than courier?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Airport-to-airport cargo is better than courier when fast intercity movement and terminal delivery matter more than routine door-to-door routing. It can reduce hub transfers and support urgent cargo delivery across airport-connected cities."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why does regular courier fail for urgent shipments?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Regular courier can fail for urgent shipments because it optimizes parcel volume, hub routing, and scheduled linehaul. Mission-critical cargo needs airport-linked movement, air cargo timing, real-time monitoring, and human operations coordination."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is air cargo faster than surface transport?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Air cargo can be faster than surface transport for urgent intercity delivery because the long-distance leg moves by flight. Feasibility still depends on pickup timing, airport cargo handling requirements, cargo eligibility, and destination support."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why does same-day air cargo cost more?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Same-day air cargo can cost more because it requires urgent human support, timing-led movement, cargo handling, air cargo movement, and active shipment updates. The cost reflects operational urgency rather than commodity parcel routing."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is air cargo timing important?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Air cargo timing timing is important because cargo must be accepted before the flight or cargo terminal deadline. Missing the timing can shift the shipment to a later flight or a different movement plan."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who should use PORTADOR SOS?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR SOS is for manufacturers, aviation teams, pharma teams, event teams, legal firms, electronics businesses, travelers, students, SMEs, startups, and high-value cargo clients facing urgent shipment today requirements."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which shipments are suitable for same-day air cargo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Suitable same-day air cargo includes urgent business documents, machine parts, aircraft spare parts logistics, medical equipment cargo, electronics cargo, event material emergency delivery, excess baggage, and high-value cargo delivery."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which cargo requires airline approval?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Cargo requiring airline approval can include dangerous goods cargo, lithium battery cargo, battery cargo by air, chemical cargo approval, regulated air cargo, restricted goods air cargo, oversized cargo, and certain high-value or sensitive shipments."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR SOS help if regular courier is too slow?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR SOS can check airport-linked movement, next flight out logistics, hand carry, or air cargo charter feasibility when regular courier is too slow for the shipment deadline."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does PORTADOR SOS reduce hub delays?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR SOS prioritizes airport-linked movement, next-flight-out planning, and direct operational coordination where feasible instead of defaulting to multi-hub parcel sorting flows."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What does human operations coordination mean?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A human operations desk reviews the shipment, checks service feasibility, tracks timing constraints, coordinates pickup or airport support, and responds when flight, documentation, or receiver-side conditions change."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can this help prevent business downtime?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR SOS is designed for shipments where a delayed part, document, device, sample, or baggage item can create operational loss, missed commitments, or expensive downtime."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is same-day delivery always possible?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Same-day movement depends on pickup readiness, air cargo timing, airline availability, cargo acceptance, destination timing, and final delivery. PORTADOR SOS checks the fastest feasible option before confirming."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR SOS support urgent intercity delivery?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Urgent intercity delivery is a core use case, especially across airport-connected cities where air movement can outperform surface transport or routine overnight courier timelines."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What makes PORTADOR SOS premium?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR SOS is premium because it focuses on operational urgency, air-linked movement, compliance-aware cargo review, human support, and deadline protection rather than commodity parcel volume."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How can I send excess baggage by air?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"You can send excess baggage by air when the bags or boxes are properly packed, declared, and accepted for airport-linked cargo movement. PORTADOR SOS checks weight, contents, pickup or airport support timing, air cargo timing, and destination support before support."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How can I ship lithium battery cargo by air?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Lithium battery cargo can move by air only when the battery type, rating, packing, documents, and airline rules allow it. PORTADOR SOS verifies MSDS or declarations where required, reviews compliance, and confirms service feasibility before movement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When can dangerous goods or battery cargo move by air?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Dangerous goods or battery cargo can move by air only after approval, documentation, packing, and regulatory compliance review are cleared. Final movement depends on commodity classification, MSDS or declaration, service feasibility, handling requirements, and approval."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which batteries need declaration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Battery declaration may be needed for standalone lithium batteries, batteries packed with equipment, batteries contained in equipment, and certain electronic devices. The exact requirement depends on chemistry, watt-hour rating, quantity, packing, airline rules, and service feasibility."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which cities are best connected by airport cargo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Major airport-connected cities such as Delhi, Mumbai, Bangalore, Chennai, Hyderabad, Pune, Ahmedabad, and Kolkata are usually stronger for urgent airport cargo. Feasibility still depends on pickup readiness, air cargo timing, cargo acceptance, and destination support timing."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR SOS move urgent business documents?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR SOS can coordinate urgent business documents, tender files, legal papers, commercial contracts, and confidential submissions through same-day air cargo, hand carry, or airport-linked movement where feasible."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When should a business escalate urgent shipment movement?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A business should escalate urgent shipment movement when delay can cause production loss, machine downtime, aircraft downtime, missed tender submission, event failure, customer escalation, or emergency replacement failure. PORTADOR SOS then checks the fastest feasible air-linked plan."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is emergency logistics?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Emergency logistics is shipment support for cargo that has an immediate operational consequence if delayed. It focuses on human support, service feasibility, air cargo timing, shipment updates, and destination support instead of routine parcel flow."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is time-critical logistics?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Time-critical logistics is deadline-led cargo movement where speed, feasibility, custody, compliance, and human support matter more than routine network scheduling. PORTADOR SOS applies this approach to same-day air cargo, NFO movement, airport cargo, and mission-critical shipments."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which Indian cities does PORTADOR SOS support?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR SOS focuses on major airport-linked Indian cities including Delhi, Mumbai, Bangalore, Chennai, Hyderabad, Pune, Ahmedabad, and Kolkata, with service feasibility checked per shipment."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR SOS help with urgent business shipments?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR SOS is designed for urgent B2B shipments, manufacturing parts, aviation spares, legal documents, electronics, event cargo, and high-value movement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What does no hub delays mean?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No avoidable hub delays means PORTADOR SOS prioritizes direct airport-linked planning where feasible instead of defaulting to multi-hub parcel sorting cycles used by high-volume courier networks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who should use PORTADOR BLACK?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR BLACK is for founders, CEOs, HNIs, UHNWIs, family offices, legal teams, and high-value cargo customers who need hand carry, OBC, runner, VIP, confidential, or short-notice logistics."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When should businesses use PORTADOR EXPRESS?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Businesses should use PORTADOR EXPRESS for next business day or second business day premium air cargo when a shipment is important, B2B, and air-priority, but not a same-day emergency."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is PORTADOR GLOBAL?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR GLOBAL is urgent international import and export air cargo coordination for premium cross-border air freight, documentation-aware movement, compliance review, and time-sensitive global shipment planning."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR help with same-day delivery?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR SOS can support same-day delivery where cargo readiness, documents, serviceability, and available air movement allow. Share the city pair, deadline, cargo type, weight, dimensions, and pickup details for urgent feasibility review."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is air cargo movement?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Air cargo movement means eligible goods travel through air freight channels instead of routine surface transport. It is useful for urgent intercity shipments, business-critical parts, excess baggage, documents, medical cargo, and high-priority B2B cargo."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is airport cargo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Airport cargo is shipment movement connected to airport cargo facilities and air freight options. It can help urgent cargo move faster between major cities where serviceability, documentation, cargo type, and acceptance conditions allow."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When is air cargo better than courier?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Air cargo is better than courier when the shipment has a hard deadline, long intercity distance, business downtime risk, or urgent receiver requirement. Routine courier is suitable for normal parcels without immediate time pressure."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR ship excess baggage?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR can support excess baggage shipping for domestic and international travel situations where contents are eligible, packed correctly, documented, and accepted for movement. Share baggage count, weight, route, deadline, and contents."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can students send baggage with PORTADOR?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Students can request baggage movement support for relocation, college moves, missed baggage situations, or urgent personal goods. Feasibility depends on contents, packing, documents, pickup city, destination, and timeline."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR help with relocation cargo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR can check relocation cargo when items are air-eligible and time-sensitive. It is best for urgent personal goods, student baggage, priority cartons, documents, electronics, and selected household items, not bulk household shifting."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR move personal goods?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR can check personal goods where items are legally permitted, packed correctly, declared accurately, and serviceable. Restricted or prohibited items cannot be accepted, and some categories may need documentation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can household items move by air cargo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Selected household items can move by air cargo when they are permitted, properly packed, and documented. Large-volume household shifting is usually better suited to surface movement, while urgent boxes or essential items may be reviewed."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR ship laptops?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Laptop shipping can be checked where packing, invoice details, battery declaration, and serviceability are acceptable. Lithium batteries inside devices may require declaration and airline approval depending on quantity and conditions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR ship mobile phones?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Mobile phone shipping can be checked if the device is properly packed, declared, and accepted under applicable battery and electronics rules. Quantity, invoice value, and lithium battery conditions may affect acceptance."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can dangerous goods move with PORTADOR?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR can review dangerous goods cargo, but movement depends on classification, documentation, packing, approvals, and service feasibility. MSDS, declaration, invoice, and compliance details may be required before acceptance."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can lithium batteries move by air?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Lithium batteries can move by air only when the battery type, rating, packing, quantity, documents, and approvals meet applicable rules. PORTADOR can check battery cargo but cannot accept it without compliance review."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does PORTADOR provide warehousing?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR may check temporary holding or warehousing support for selected shipments where location, duration, cargo type, compliance requirements, and urgency allow. Share shipment details for availability review."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR arrange reverse pickup?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Reverse pickup can be checked where pickup address, cargo readiness, documents, packing, and serviceability allow. Share pickup contact, destination, cargo details, and deadline."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR support import shipments?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR GLOBAL can check urgent import shipment support for time-sensitive international cargo. Feasibility depends on documents, customs status, commodity type, consignee readiness, compliance requirements, and available premium air freight options."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does PORTADOR handle customs?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR can guide customers on shipment documentation requirements and check international cargo support. Customs processes depend on commodity type, documents, duties, taxes, regulations, and appointed clearance arrangements."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I track my shipment?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"You can request tracking support by sharing your booking reference, shipment details, or contact number. PORTADOR will check the available shipment status and share updates through the operations desk."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How fast can pickup happen?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Pickup timing depends on city, location, cargo readiness, documents, packing, traffic, and service availability. For urgent requests, share complete details immediately so PORTADOR can check the fastest feasible support."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is delivery timing confirmed?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Delivery timing is confirmed only after cargo details, serviceability, documentation, acceptance requirements, and receiver availability are reviewed. PORTADOR avoids false guarantees for shipments affected by external conditions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is volumetric weight?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Volumetric weight is a billing weight based on package size rather than only actual weight. Large lightweight boxes may be charged by volumetric weight because they occupy more cargo space."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is E-Way Bill required?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"E-Way Bill may be required for commercial goods depending on invoice value, commodity type, origin, destination, and applicable GST rules. Customers should provide required tax documents before shipment movement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does PORTADOR provide insurance?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Insurance or declared-value protection may be available only when agreed and documented before shipment movement. High-value cargo should be declared accurately, and customers should review liability terms before booking."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is FOV?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"FOV means Freight on Value or declared-value handling charges for eligible shipments. Where applicable, FOV may be charged based on invoice value and accepted terms before shipment movement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is Carrier Risk?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Carrier Risk is a declared-value risk option that may be available at 5% of invoice value for eligible shipments, subject to written acceptance and policy conditions. It must be confirmed before booking."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is Own Risk?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Own Risk means the shipment moves without additional declared-value carrier risk coverage beyond standard liability terms. Customers should review policy limits before booking high-value or sensitive shipments."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which items are prohibited?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Prohibited items include goods banned by law, unsafe items, undeclared dangerous goods, restricted substances, and items not accepted by relevant carriers or authorities. Customers must review the Restricted Goods page before booking."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does the refund policy work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Refund eligibility depends on booking status, cancellation timing, service attempt, shipment acceptance, and policy terms. Customers should review the Booking & Refund Policy for liability, cancellation, claim, and refund conditions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What payment methods are accepted?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Payment methods may include bank transfer, UPI, or other accepted business payment options shared during booking. Shipment movement may require payment confirmation before service execution."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR provide a GST invoice?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR can provide GST invoice support for eligible commercial bookings where correct billing details, GSTIN, company name, address, and shipment information are provided."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR support commercial B2B shipments?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. PORTADOR supports urgent commercial and B2B shipments such as machine parts, electronics, samples, documents, medical equipment, aviation spares, event material, and high-value cargo where serviceability allows."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can medical cargo move with PORTADOR?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Medical cargo can be checked where the item is permitted, documented, packed correctly, and accepted for movement. Temperature sensitivity, device value, urgency, and compliance requirements must be declared clearly."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can PORTADOR move high-value cargo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"PORTADOR can check high-value cargo where declaration, packaging, documentation, receiver details, risk terms, and serviceability are clear. High-value shipments should be declared accurately before acceptance."}}]}a:["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","main",null,{"children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$1d"}}],"$L1e","$L1f","$L20"]}],null,"$L21"]}]
